---
// Problem.astro
---
<section class="section" id="problem">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-label">⚠ The Problem</div>
      <h2>Three crises. One frozen AI project.</h2>
      <p>Banks are trapped between engineering teams pushing forward and risk teams holding them back. The result is millions in stranded investment.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="problem-grid">
      <!-- Problem 1 -->
      <div class="problem-card card" id="problem-purgatory">
        <div class="problem-icon" style="--icon-color: #f59e0b; --icon-bg: rgba(245,158,11,0.1);">
          <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-stat">$5M+</div>
        <div class="problem-stat-label">average AI initiative frozen in sandbox</div>
        <h3>"Pilot Purgatory"</h3>
        <p>The Head of AI Platform built working agentic workflows. Then the Risk Committee vetoed production deployment. The AI sits unused — costing millions in missed savings every quarter.</p>
        <div class="problem-quote">
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.4"><path d="M3 21c3 0 7-1 7-8V5c0-1.25-.756-2.017-2-2H4c-1.25 0-2 .75-2 1.972V11c0 1.25.75 2 2 2 1 0 1 0 1 1v1c0 1-1 2-2 2s-1 .008-1 1.031V20c0 1 0 1 1 1z"/><path d="M15 21c3 0 7-1 7-8V5c0-1.25-.757-2.017-2-2h-4c-1.25 0-2 .75-2 1.972V11c0 1.25.75 2 2 2h.75c0 2.25.25 4-2.75 4v3c0 1 0 1 1 1z"/></svg>
          <em>"We can't deploy it — the auditors need to understand every decision the AI makes, and we have no way to show them."</em>
          <span class="quote-attr">— Head of AI Platform, Tier 1.5 Bank</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Problem 2 -->
      <div class="problem-card card" id="problem-dora">
        <div class="problem-icon" style="--icon-color: #ef4444; --icon-bg: rgba(239,68,68,0.1);">
          <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-stat">4 hours</div>
        <div class="problem-stat-label">DORA initial incident reporting window</div>
        <h3>The DORA Clock</h3>
        <p>Under DORA Article 5, when an AI agent hallucinates an unauthorized action it's an ICT incident. Banks have 4 hours to file an initial report — but engineers need 3 days to reconstruct what happened.</p>
        <div class="problem-quote">
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.4"><path d="M3 21c3 0 7-1 7-8V5c0-1.25-.756-2.017-2-2H4c-1.25 0-2 .75-2 1.972V11c0 1.25.75 2 2 2 1 0 1 0 1 1v1c0 1-1 2-2 2s-1 .008-1 1.031V20c0 1 0 1 1 1z"/><path d="M15 21c3 0 7-1 7-8V5c0-1.25-.757-2.017-2-2h-4c-1.25 0-2 .75-2 1.972V11c0 1.25.75 2 2 2h.75c0 2.25.25 4-2.75 4v3c0 1 0 1 1 1z"/></svg>
          <em>"If this AI makes a mistake and I can't explain why to the ESA within the window, that's my personal liability."</em>
          <span class="quote-attr">— Chief Risk Officer, ECB-supervised institution</span>
        </div>
        <div class="dora-fine-note">
          <span class="badge badge-red">⚡ Up to €1M personal fine</span>
          <span>under DORA Article 5(4)</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Problem 3 -->
      <div class="problem-card card" id="problem-vacuum">
        <div class="problem-icon" style="--icon-color: #3b82f6; --icon-bg: rgba(59,130,246,0.1);">
          <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><line x1="8" y1="21" x2="16" y2="21"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12" y2="21"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-stat">0</div>
        <div class="problem-stat-label">existing tools designed for this problem</div>
        <h3>The Governance Vacuum</h3>
        <p>Datadog tells you the system crashed. ServiceNow logs traditional model metadata. Neither can map the <em>business context</em> of why a probabilistic AI agent made a specific, multi-step decision.</p>
        <div class="alternatives-list">
          <div class="alt-item">
            <span class="alt-tool">Datadog / Splunk</span>
            <span class="alt-verdict">Shows latency, not decisions</span>
          </div>
          <div class="alt-item">
            <span class="alt-tool">ServiceNow GRC</span>
            <span class="alt-verdict">Static inventory, not runtime traces</span>
          </div>
          <div class="alt-item">
            <span class="alt-tool">Manual + Word Doc</span>
            <span class="alt-verdict">Days of work, legally indefensible</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Bottom callout -->
    <div class="problem-bottom">
      <div class="problem-callout">
        <div class="callout-icon">✈</div>
        <div>
          <strong>The Black Box Metaphor</strong>
          <p>A flight recorder doesn't prevent crashes — it survives them and provides the exact, undeniable chronology of what the pilot did. Banks need the same thing for their AI agents.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
.problem-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
  gap: 1.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
}

.problem-card {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.75rem;
}

.problem-icon {
  width: 56px;
  height: 56px;
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  background: var(--icon-bg, var(--color-cyan-dim));
  color: var(--icon-color, var(--color-cyan));
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.problem-stat {
  font-family: var(--font-heading);
  font-size: 2.4rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  line-height: 1;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-cyan), var(--color-blue));
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  background-clip: text;
}
.problem-stat-label {
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  color: var(--color-text-dim);
  margin-top: -0.5rem;
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
}

.problem-card h3 { font-size: 1.25rem; margin-top: 0.25rem; }
.problem-card p  { font-size: 0.92rem; flex: 1; }

.problem-quote {
  background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
  border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  padding: 0.75rem;
  border-left: 2px solid var(--color-border-hover);
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.4rem;
  margin-top: auto;
}
.problem-quote em { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); font-style: italic; line-height: 1.5; }
.quote-attr { font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--color-text-dim); font-family: var(--font-mono); }

.dora-fine-note {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.6rem;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  color: var(--color-text-dim);
  margin-top: auto;
}

.alternatives-list {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.4rem;
  margin-top: auto;
}
.alt-item {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.5rem;
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  padding: 0.4rem 0.6rem;
  background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
  border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
}
.alt-tool {
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
  font-size: 0.72rem;
}
.alt-verdict {
  color: var(--color-red);
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  text-align: right;
}

.problem-bottom { display: flex; justify-content: center; }
.problem-callout {
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  gap: 1.25rem;
  background: var(--color-surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  border-top: 2px solid var(--color-cyan);
  border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
  max-width: 680px;
}
.callout-icon {
  font-size: 2.5rem;
  line-height: 1;
  filter: grayscale(0.3);
}
.problem-callout strong {
  font-family: var(--font-heading);
  font-size: 1rem;
  color: var(--color-text);
  display: block;
  margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
}
.problem-callout p { font-size: 0.9rem; margin: 0; }
</style>
